==English==

===Noun===
'''[[differential]] [[diagnosis]]'''
# {{medicine}}:  The process by which a [[physician]] produces a [[diagnosis]] that explains a patient's [[symptom]]s.
# {{medicine}}:  The part of this process concerned with determining, from a set of possible candidates, which [[disease]] is causing the symptoms.
# {{medicine}}:  A list of the common causes of a primary symptom.
##:The differential diagnosis for febrile patients with a rash is extensive.[http://www.aafp.org/afp/20000815/804.html]